1.title: The Weddings
1.plot: Three young couples decide to take a leap of love and transition from teen sweethearts to husband and wife. Halie and George, both members of the Mormon Church have only been dating for four months. Brenda and Travis have opposing beliefs and values and have been dating for less than a year after meeting in college.

2.title: Honeymoons and Tears
2.plot: We follow the three couples as they navigate intimacy inside and outside the bedroom. Halie and George, nervous but giddy, spend their first night together. Brenda and Travis head off to honeymoon in Mexico, while Emma and Joey honeymoon in Canada and then start their life together in Oregon.

3.title: Leaving the Nest
3.plot: Now that the honeymoons are over, it's time for our couples to set up their homes. Halie and George move to Utah, Travis and Brenda finally get to move into together after being separated for two months. Emma and Joey start to house hunt.

4.title: Baby Talk
4.plot: The couples have settled in and babies are on everyone's mind. Halie and George, get their first taste of parenting when babysitting their 4-year-old nephew. Brenda and Travis have a pregnancy scare, while Emma and Joey shop for their friend's baby shower.

5.title: Marriage Meets Money
5.plot: The couples adjust to shared finances and responsibilities. Halie and George meet with a financial advisor. Brenda and Travis go over their finances they realize that they are not on the same page. Emma and Joey meet with a mortgage broker to get pre approved for a loan.

6.title: Married with Friends
6.plot: The couples attempt to balance time with family, friends and their married life. While George comfortably returns to his life in Utah, Halie is homesick for her family and friends back in Arizona.

7.title: Communication Breakdown
7.plot: The couples seek advice from family and professionals on how to improve their communication skills. When Halie's family visits, George feels insecure about her close ties to them. Brenda and Travis visit a marriage counselor to discuss their opposing beliefs and values. Emma is upset at Joey for not taking on household responsibilities.

8.title: Breakthroughs
8.plot: The couple's differences come to a head, and they must make some important decisions together. Halie and George decide whether or not to move back to Arizona. Brenda and Travis decide which moral values are right for their family. Emma and Joey determine if counseling is the best next step for their relationship.

imdb.plot outline: You've got to be 16 to drive, 17 to enlist, and 18 to vote. Teenage Newlyweds literally asks: is there an age limit on love? By showcasing several pairs of young engaged couples with different backgrounds and ideals as they head to their wedding, we may find the answer lies in the subsequent honeymoon episode.
